description: A thicket of kowhai saplings. It looked like they were a case of flood-disturbance-induced recruitment. They were at the bottom of what looked like a flood channel. There was debris and silt deposited and the saplings were mostly pretty uniform in age. I guess the seed was washed in there from those mature kowhai to the west along with the silt. It was good to see a disturbance regime that was working as you'd hope - at least to some extent.
